  "prompt": "Which one is grammatically correct: pick up someone at the airport or from the airport?",
  "response": "Both \"pick up someone at the airport\" and \"pick up someone from the airport\" are grammatically correct, but they can carry slightly different connotations. \n\n- \"Pick up someone at the airport\" typically emphasizes the location where you will meet the person.\n- \"Pick up someone from the airport\" often emphasizes the action of retrieving the person as they arrive.\n\nIn everyday conversation, both phrases are commonly used and understood.",
